cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with identifying network topology from energy measurements in a power distribution network. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a data-driven approach to efficiently operate the power distribution network. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves the application of Principal Component Analysis (PCA) to infer the network topology. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a novel approach to identify the network topology. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper involves the interpretation of PCA in a graph-theoretic manner to infer the network topology.
